reviews.text: The food is not bad in average

Firstly the place is hardly what I would consider ‘Vietnamese’ but anyway at least hoped it would be decent simple dishes. Instead it’s complicated mess of oily/greasy frozen fried dishes. All three dishes ordered were mostly dripping in pool of oil. Burnt on outside and oily cool on inside. Ordered coconut coffee but got milk tea instead. Only positive was background music was ok. For a real Vietnamese flavour it would not be a place to recommend.
New Vietnam restaurant. Boss taking care of business. Food sophisticatedly prepared. Should try.

Rating based on comparison with restaurants available nearby:
(Overall: 3.55, Rating based on closest whole number)

Food: 3.8, The food here I genuinely find good. However I must say that the portions here are quite overwhelming for one person. It is more tailored to physical laborers or athletes, than office workers and ladies.

Decor: 3.5, Some effort has gone into making the place look friendly.

Comfort: 3.5, seating is fairly comfy.

Service: 3, Nothing notable can be given. Generally normal waiters.

Price/Value: 4, Fantastic value for good tasting food, BUT usually you have to order one meal to split among two people. The sheer quantity of each dish is huge and so you can simply split it with the other person. Either split with someone, or take half the meal away in a box. Either way its two portions worth.

Sanitation:  3.5. Generally a clean feeling here. Floors mopped, no bits of food littered around, utensils are usually clean. Nothing to give the impression that you may come away sick. What is to be expected of any restaurant.

Recommendations to Owner: Reduce portion sizes and price appropriately. A lot of people seemingly cannot finish their plates due to the excess! Also many dishes make heavy use of oil and there are some dishes that are rather strong in taste. Perhaps add some dishes that are less heavy in taste and oil.
Just awful.. the broth is just lukewarm.. this is what I left. How can it be still open with such terrible food?

reviews.text: Always comfortable, always tasty, always persistent and most of all, constant with heart💓
Nice place n delicious food

Fantastic FOOD & Service!!!!!!
 Every single dish was made by the owner and the chef, with so much LOVE and passion!  We had our family gathering there and they treated us with royalty!  I can totally feel that they are truly the business with heart!  I will be back... support local business especially people like you guys! 💝💝💝💝

Had lunch with my hubby and my little one at Fantasy Kitchen, Shatin last week.   We live nearby and always pass by the restaurant but never got the chance to give it a try.   
The lunch menu is very good for value, range from $6x - $8x.   A lot of selection. my hubby ordered a Sea Urchin mushroom risotto and i ordered fish with pesto sauce and mashed potato.   Both dishes were wonderfully made!!   We were so surprised that a small shop in our neighbourhood makes good food!    I would recommend this restaurant to everyone!
sincere and comfortable

是大酒店價錢，與所在地花園城有點格格不入，可能是做遊客生意的。鳳爪HK$78, 只有兩隻半鳳爪。菠蘿抄飯，飯無乜料，蝦魚都無味，HK$95. 串燒牛肉可以，HK$55 三串。服務，唔好諗。

仲唔收信用卡！

食物差，坐位細，服務差!!!
叫了一個春卷 油淋淋，之後四季豆咸到食咸魚咁，同四眼男經理講佢答係咁，馬拉炒係咸！即是叫佢收走佢 之後都無心機食野
差差差
都ok啦食物，款式都幾多揀
